Japan Beats U.S. to Earn First Women’s World Cup Soccer Title

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-07-17T21:22:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-17/japan-beats-u-s-to-win-first-women-s-world-cup.html
Japan  beat the U.S. in a penalty
kick shootout to win its first Women’s World Cup soccer
championship, the second international sports title in a week to
boost a nation still recovering from an earthquake and nuclear
disaster in March.  The teams were tied 2-2 after 90 minutes of regulation play
and 30 minutes of extra time in  Frankfurt . Japan won the penalty
shootout 3-1.      To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net  